The paper deals with the problem of distance and reachability oracles in graphs, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also uses techniques from symbolic computation (cs.SY) and numerical analysis (cs.NA) to develop their algorithm. Additionally, the paper involves a lot of mathematical analysis and optimization, which could also place it under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
